{"type": "root", "attrs": {"type": "node", "context": "vop", "internal": "halo", "icon": "VOP/halo", "version": null, "namespace": null}, "body": [{"level": 0, "type": "title", "indent": 0, "text": ["Halo"], "extent": [59, 68]}, {"type": "summary", "indent": 0, "text": ["Generates a soft halo effect to be used in the Fog context, and\noutputs color and alpha."], "extent": [68, 165]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["This operator generates a soft halo effect to be used in the Fog\ncontext, and outputs color and alpha."], "extent": [165, 269]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["Unlike Glow, which is meant for glows around lights, flames, and other\nhot point sources, this operator produces a generic, white-light glow."], "extent": [269, 412]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["The higher the density of the fog, the smaller the radius of the halo."], "extent": [412, 484]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["The Fog Point Size (", {"type": "code", "text": ["fptsize"]}, ") controls the size of the fog\u2019s center."], "extent": [484, 555]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["The Fog Color (", {"type": "code", "text": ["fcolor"]}, ") is multiplied by the Opacity (Of) before being\nmixed with the Surface Color, so you do not have to take opacity into\naccount yourself."], "extent": [555, 716]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["If the Surface Position (", {"type": "code", "text": ["P"]}, "), Position of Eye (", {"type": "code", "text": ["Eye"]}, "), Surface Color (", {"type": "code", "text": ["Cf"]}, ")\nSurface Opacity (", {"type": "code", "text": ["Of"]}, "), and Surface Alpha (", {"type": "code", "text": ["Af"]}, ") inputs are not connected,\nthe global variables by the same names will be used instead. If you need\nto access the global variables directly, they are available from the\n", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/vop/global", "type": "link", "text": ["Global Variables"], "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/global.html"}, " operator."], "extent": [716, 1056]}, {"type": "para", "indent": 0, "text": ["For a simple halo, connect the color output (", {"type": "code", "text": ["color"]}, ") and the alpha output\n(", {"type": "code", "text": ["alpha"]}, ") to the ", {"type": "code", "text": ["Cf"]}, " and respectively ", {"type": "code", "text": ["Af"]}, " inputs of the ", {"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/vop/output", "type": "link", "text": ["Output Variables"], "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/output.html"}, "\noperator."], "extent": [1056, 1237]}, {"level": 1, "id": "related", "container": true, "type": "related_section", "indent": 0, "role": "section", "extent": [1237, 1246], "body": [{"type": "bullet_group", "body": [{"blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "indent": 4, "text": [{"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/vop/global", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/global.html"}], "extent": [1246, 1270]}, {"blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "indent": 4, "text": [{"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/vop/glow", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/glow.html"}], "extent": [1270, 1292]}, {"blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "indent": 4, "text": [{"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/vop/illuminance", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/illuminance.html"}], "extent": [1292, 1321]}, {"blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "indent": 4, "text": [{"scheme": "Node", "value": "/nodes/vop/output", "type": "link", "text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/output.html"}], "extent": [1321, 1346]}], "container": true}], "text": "Related"}], "title": ["Halo"], "summary": ["Generates a soft halo effect to be used in the Fog context, and\noutputs color and alpha."]}